Post the lynching of Deputy SP Mohammed Ayub Pandith in Kashmir, certain sections of public and some politicians have raised concerns about the situation in the Valley turning from bad to worse. However, Union Home Secretary believes lynching incidents are over-hyped and do not deserve the kind of attention they have received.While speaking in Jaipur, Rajiv Mehrishi, the Union Home Secretary, stated, "I don't think it (hate crime) is new in India. While condemning the incident as regretful, the Union Home Secretary claimed it won't change the entire complexity of the Kashmir situation.He also said that an entire paradigm shift in policing is needed to drastically improve the situation in the country. 